title: Monitoring Pivotal Redis for PCF&reg; with Dingo Prometheus™
---

Dingo Prometheus™ allows you to monitor your [Pivotal Redis for PCF&reg;](https://network.pivotal.io/products/p-redis/) installation. It comes with a set of predefined **Alerts** and **Dashboards** for Redis.

## <a id="monitoring-p-redis-configuration"></a>Configuration

In order to enable **Alerts** and **Dashboards** for Pivotal Redis for PCF&reg, perform the following steps:

1. In Pivotal Ops Manager, navigate to **Dingo Prometheus™ > Settings > Monitoring**.

2. Enable the **Monitor Redis for PCF&reg?** option:

    ![monitoring-p-redis-prometheus-configuration](images/monitoring-p-redis-prometheus-configuration.png)

3. Click **Save**.

4. Return to the Ops Manager dashboard via the **< Installation Dashboard** link at the top left and press **Apply Changes**.

The install process generally requires several minutes to complete. Once completed, Dingo Prometheus™ will start monitoring your Pivotal Redis for PCF&reg; installation.

## <a id="monitoring-p-redis-alerts"></a>Alerts

Dingo Prometheus™ comes with a set of predefined alerts for Pivotal Redis for PCF&reg;.

### <a id="monitoring-p-redis-nodes-alerts"></a>Nodes

Nodes alerts monitors your **Redis Nodes** status and emits alerts depending on the node state:

![monitoring-p-redis-nodes-alerts](images/monitoring-p-redis-nodes-alerts.png)

| Alert | Description |
| ----- | ----------- |
| **PRedisNoClientsConnected** | It will emit a **warning** alert if a Redis node had **NO clients connected** during the last 30 minutes |
| **PRedisRejectedConnections** | It will emit a **warning** alert if a Redis node had **rejected connections** during the last 30 minutes |
| **PRedisHighMemoryFragmentation** | It will emit a **warning** alert if a Redis node had **more than 30% of memory fragmentation** during the last 30 minutes |
| **PRedisHighAOFRewriteTime** | It will emit a **warning** alert if the last **AOF rewrite** took **more than 10 minutes** during the last 30 minutes |
| **PRedisHighRDBBgSaveTime** | It will emit a **warning** alert if the last **RDB bgsave** took **more than 10 minutes** during the last 30 minutes |

### <a id="monitoring-p-redis-service-broker-alerts"></a>Service Broker

Service Broker alerts monitors your **Redis Service Broker** status and emits alerts depending on its state:

![monitoring-p-redis-alerts](images/monitoring-p-redis-service-broker-alerts.png)

| Alert | Description |
| ----- | ----------- |
| **PRedisServiceBrokerDedicatedPlanLowVMsAvailable** | It will emit a **warning** alert if there are **less than 10%** of VMs available for the **Dedicated Plan** during the last 30 minutes |
| **PRedisServiceBrokerDedicatedPlanNoVMsAvailable** | It will emit a **critical** alert if **there are NOT any VMs available** for the **Dedicated Plan** during the last 30 minutes |
| **PRedisServiceBrokerSharedPlanLowInstancesAvailable** | It will emit a **warning** alert if there are **less than 10%** of Instances available for the **Shared Plan** during the last 30 minutes |
| **PRedisServiceBrokerSharedPlanNoInstancesAvailable** | It will emit a **critical** alert if **there are NOT any Instances available** for the **Shared Plan** during the last 30 minutes |
| **PRedisServiceBrokerOnDemandLowInstancesAvailable** | It will emit a **warning** alert if there are **less than 10%** of Instances available for the **On Demand Service Broker** during the last 30 minutes |
| **PRedisServiceBrokerOnDemandNoInstancesAvailable** | It will emit a **critical** alert if **there are NOT any Instances available** for the **On Demand Service Broker** during the last 30 minutes |

